```

If you’re using a different mapping library (e.g., Mapbox GL JS), the principle is the same: assign a class or ID to the tooltip element and target it with CSS. You can also modify the tooltip’s HTML content directly if you need richer styling (e.g., adding icons or line breaks).

Remember to load your custom CSS after the library’s default stylesheet so your rules take precedence, or use `!important` sparingly if needed.

